```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized: Port Created

    Uninitialized --> Ready: initialize(config)
    Ready --> Connected: connect(target_port_id)
    Connected --> Busy: send/receive(message)
    Busy --> Connected: Operation Complete
    Connected --> Disconnected: disconnect()
    Disconnected --> Ready: cleanup() + reconnect

    Ready --> Error: Initialization Failed
    Connected --> Error: Socket Error
    Busy --> Error: Unrecoverable Error
    Error --> [*]: shutdown()

    note right of Uninitialized
        Port created but not initialized
        No resources allocated
    end note

    note right of Busy
        Processing messages
        Stats tracked
    end note

    note right of Error
        Unrecoverable socket errors
        Requires shutdown
    end note
```

## States
- **Uninitialized**: Port created, no resources allocated
- **Ready**: Initialized and waiting for connection
- **Connected**: Active connection to target port
- **Busy**: Processing messages (send/receive)
- **Disconnected**: Connection closed, can reconnect
- **Error**: Unrecoverable error, requires shutdown

## Transitions
- **initialize()**: Allocates resources, enters Ready state
- **connect()**: Establishes connection to target port
- **send/receive()**: Transitions to Busy, updates stats
- **disconnect()**: Closes connection, returns to Ready after cleanup
- **unrecoverable error**: Direct to Error state

## Guards
- **State validation**: Operations only valid in specific states
- **Connection limits**: Max concurrent connections enforced
- **Error recovery**: Only reconnection from Disconnected, not from Error
